<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 12) This is a PvE server, NOT a PvP server.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
This rule here makes all the difference, because it means that NOTHING has changed with the basic objective in EQ. In other words they are saying that people will in no way be able to influence their enviroment, and that no matter how much you manage to disrupt the balance of power, it will have no effect whatsoever.<br>
Furthermore, roleplaying will be just as difficult on the RP server as on a non-rp server because we cannot attack people whom we think deserves to be run through, but have to go through the rigors of a duel or guildwar in order to lay hands on our enemies.<br>
Think of it: Even though I had an entire legion of Dark Elves at my command I would STILL be unable to kill a single palsy little paladin who was killing guards in Nektulos.<br>
<br>
Another example: It would be logical to think that if I managed to unite 200 Dark Elves into one single guild whose sole objective was to reduce Freeport to ruins, then my guild should have some basic influence on the enviroment in EQ. But, no matter how many times I attack Freeport and kill everyone in sight, no matter how many good paladins my guild slaughter, it will all be for naught.<br>
 <br>
Because the server will STILL be PvE, so everything we kill will just respawn and nothing will have changed.<br>
